\fs24
\b IH35 ERP — Requests Not Yet Implemented (and Why)\b0\par
\par
This document lists requests you made that are not implemented yet (or only partially implemented), plus the most direct reason.\par
\par
\b 1) ERP-wide UI / Navigation (QuickBooks-like)\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Sidebar redesign to navigate like QuickBooks (hover lists, deeper IA)\b0\par
Not implemented yet because it requires a top-level navigation/IA refactor across many sections, otherwise we risk breaking existing workflows and creating duplicated entry points.\par
\par
\b Maintenance sidebar sub-items (Internal Mechanic, External Mechanic, Roadside Service, Parts Purchases)\b0\par
Not implemented yet because it depends on the navigation refactor and requires defining each flow (what auto-fills, what is mandatory, and what is created) plus data-model alignment for parts purchases.\par
\par
\b Reports section in the sidebar with all report types\b0\par
Not implemented yet because the report inventory and a consistent report UX (filters, date range, search, export) are not yet centralized into a report center.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 2) Search\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Global search bar in main navigation\b0\par
Not implemented yet because we must define which entities are searchable (loads, vendors, assets, bills, work orders, maintenance records, bill payments, etc.), add a query/index endpoint, and implement ranking + deep links.\par
\par
\b Per-section search in each section\b0\par
Not implemented yet because search/filter behavior is currently ad-hoc per panel; it needs a standardized pattern and wiring across multiple sections.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 3) Maintenance — Shop queue + Integrity “data grid” modernization\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Upgrade Awaiting service / In progress / Completed + Integrity boxes into a professional data grid with date + search controls\b0\par
Partially implemented previously (labels updated); the full grid/table behavior requires new table UI, filter controls, and wiring those controls to the underlying data and endpoints.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 4) Reporting controls everywhere\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b “In all areas where there is data showing, a report type should allow us to change dates.”\b0\par
Not implemented yet because only some endpoints support true date windows; making this consistent requires standard date-range state, query params, and UI controls across many panels and reports.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 5) Maintenance — Overview tab practicality\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Re-evaluate practicality of the Maintenance Overview tab\b0\par
Not implemented yet because it is an information-architecture decision (what becomes the default landing, what becomes a dashboard vs operational board) and must be redesigned with the rest of the navigation changes.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 6) “Adequate forms” for lists\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Assets, vendors, every type of list should have an adequate form\b0\par
Not implemented yet because this requires dedicated CRUD screens/drawers per entity, validation rules, persistence, and consistent UX patterns across multiple modules.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 7) Partially implemented: Bill-pay partial-payment UX polish\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b Partial bill-pay UX polish\b0\par
Partially implemented: there is open-bill selection, per-line pay amounts, remaining balance, Max fill, totals, and local logging. Still missing deeper polish such as bulk pay-full, stronger validation messaging, and faster keyboard-first batch entry.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\b 8) Environment/runtime issues (may still affect your instance)\b0\par
\pard\li360
\b “QuickBooks not connected” even though connected\b0\par
May persist due to token/realm state vs UI cache; needs runtime verification in your running instance to confirm the exact failing path.\par
\par
\b “column qbo\_linehaul\_item\_id does not exist” when creating a load\b0\par
May persist if the Postgres database migrations were not applied (or the app is pointed at a different database). This is typically a migration/state issue.\par
\par
\b Miles not calculating\b0\par
Miles calculation exists (OSRM fallback, optional PC*Miler). If geocoding/routing keys are missing or requests fail at runtime, the UI will not fill miles; this needs runtime verification on your data.\par
\pard\li0
\par
End of document.\par
}
